-- Croatia Wins 3-1 Against Ireland in Euro 2012 Group C Match
-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 2012-06-10T20:41:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-10/croatia-wins-3-1-against-ireland-in-euro-2012-group-c-match.html
Mario Mandzukic got two goals as
Croatia beat Ireland 3-1 today to lead Group C at soccer’s
European Championship after the first round of matches.  Nikica Jelavic also scored for the two-time quarterfinalist
in Poznan,  Poland , with Sean St. Ledger getting Ireland’s goal.
Defending champion Spain tied 1-1 against Italy in today’s other
game.  Croatia is making its third straight appearance at the
tournament, while Ireland last qualified in 1988. Ireland’s
Giovanni Trapattoni today became the oldest coach at a European
Championship at age 73 years, 85 days.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 James Cone  at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  